@node not19 "JUNE NEWS IN BRIEF"
                               JUNE NEWS IN BRIEF
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CLICKBOOM DROPS A BOOM
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Each copy of clickBOOM's latest masterpiece, and the biggest Amiga game ever -
Nightlong, will come with a free, full original version of Amiga Quake !!!
Moreover, it includes 68K, 060, PPC, Warp3D and QuakeWorld executables! All
unrestricted and free. Enjoy Amigans! Also, make sure to visit the clickBOOM's
site in the coming days, as they will announce who the biggest clickBOOM and
Amiga fan is. And they'll have a downloadable movie to prove it! You don't want
to miss this one, trust them.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                       TWF JULY 2000 UPDATE (OR LACK OF)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ed Collins (ed@worldfoundry.com): "Sorry folks. At the moment with some internal
changes taking place in TWF, there isn't time for a monthly news update".

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                   AMIGAVIDEOGAMES OPEN GROUP (AVOG) IS BORN
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
AVOG is a new group formed by Amiga developers, musicians and graphists. AVOG
has born to end the annoying situation of not having proper documentation and
easy to use routines when creating videogames for Amiga computers. Please, take
your time to explore the AVOS's web site at http://pc.ag0ny.com/ and think about
helping them if you can!

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                           FIRST PROGRAM WITH THE SDK
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
In a recent post to comp.sys.amiga.misc, Gary Peake <gary@amiga.com> said that
"Aaron Digulla of AROS fame seems to be the author of the very first open source
program ported under the new Amiga SDK. Aaron has ported gzip. Congratulations
to Aaron from all of us for quick work!!".

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                         PORTING CLASSIC CODE TO ELATE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
According to Gary Peake, the classic code is easier to port to Elate than
Windows although it is not a straight recompile.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                 AMIGAOS SOURCE CODE NOT TO BE FREELY RELEASED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Gary Peake: "Making the (AmigaOS classic) source publicly available is not going
to happen as far as I can see. Why give away such a valuable commodity. And if
it has no value, why do so many people want to get their hands on it?"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                 NEW YORK TIMES DELIVERS POSITIVE AMIGA ARTICLE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
New York Times has recently posted an article on the current direction of the
Amiga with some basic background information. As well it interviews Bill McEwen,
as well as Amiga Active's Editor, Andrew Korn. You can read the article at
http://www.nytimes.com/library/tech/00/06/circuits/articles/22amig.html,
although you have to sign up for the article. If you do not wish to register,
you can check out a copy of the article http://www.amigart.com/22amig.html.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                          GLQUAKE SOURCE CODE RELEASED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The source code for GLQuake and the other Quake versions have been released on
the Aminet. It seems that they don't have time anymore to make the games run
better. It is still beta and the game still has a few glitches. You can download
at:

   - ftp://de.aminet.net/pub/aminet/game/shoot/Quake68k.lha
   - ftp://de.aminet.net/pub/aminet/game/shoot/QuakePUp.lha
   - ftp://de.aminet.net/pub/aminet/game/shoot/QuakeWOS.lha
   - ftp://de.aminet.net/pub/aminet/game/shoot/Quake_src.lha
   - ftp://de.aminet.net/pub/aminet/game/shoot/QuakeWorld_src.lha
   - ftp://de.aminet.net/pub/aminet/game/shoot/GLQuake_src.lha

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                    AUTODOCVIEWER LITE V2.0 BETA 7 RELEASED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BETA release 7 of AutodocViewer Lite v2.0 is now available. This version can
correct all known autodocs files with syntax errors. More information at
http://home.c2i.net/regulus/.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                SIMPLEFTP V2.54
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A new version is up on the website, and should be available from Aminet within a
day or two. Mostly bugfixes, but one rather neat addition in that downloads can
be monitored from outside the program. An example program is available in the
downloads section, as "SimpleFTP Speed Graph". More information at
http://www.simpleftp.co.uk/.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                FOUNDATION NEWS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

   - "Foundation Gold Edition" is now available from all good Amiga stockist.
     The CD, which retails at Euro 40,50, contains both the game and the new
     Missions plus some enhancements to the game itself.
   - "Foundation: The undiscovered Land", the Mission CD for Foundation, is now
     available from all good Amiga stockist. The Mission Pack costs 25,05 Euro
     and requires a Directors Cut or the original Foundation CD to run.
   - Important Notice: Both "Foundation Gold Edition" and "Foundation: The
     undiscovered Land" have been properly produced, i.e. the game is on a
     silver CD, have professionally printed covers and comes in cellophane. If
     you come across a version that is sold to you on Gold CDRs, please get in
     touch with Epic Marketing under support@epic-marketing.de.

More information at http://www.epic-marketing.de/.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                               ATEO CONCEPTS NEWS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

   - The SCSI card for the AteoBus will be available in one week or two. Price
     will be 450FF. The card own an external SCSI port (SUB-D25) and an
     internal SCSI port (50pts). Good to plug a CD-Rom burner, a ZIP drive, or
     a scanner....
   - The prices of several Ateo products have been reduced, for instance, the
     price of the AteoNet 1, the Ethernet board for the AteoBus, is now of
     290FF instead of 390FF.
   - Ateo Concepts is still working in the scandoubler. Some problems on one
     component delay the production...

More information at http://www.ateo-concepts.com/.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                       REQUIREMENTS FOR THE SDK HARDWARE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
According to Software Hut, the new brand Amiga-SDK will run in the following
configuartion:

   - PC with 2X AGP running an AMD K6-2 500mhz, any K6-III or Athlon or INTEL,
     Pentium II 300mhz or faster
   - 128mb ram or higher
   - 10 Gig hard drive or higher
   - Sounblaster 16 bit compatible audio card (recommended Soundblaster 128)
   - Matrox AGP G400 Dual Head Video Card 16mb or 32mb (this model will be 100%
     supported in future releases of SDK, although any Linux supported AGP
     Graphics card will work in the intial release)
   - 100 base T ethernet board PCI (recommended LinkSys LNE 100TX)
   - VGA Monitor
   - Red Hat Linux 6.1 installed

More information at http://www.softhut.com/.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                  MAKE CD NEWS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Patrick Ohly (patrick@core.de) has implemented raw writing on MakeCD CD burning
software, and he will try to get a beta module with support for it finished
soon. First he has to sort out other problems with Sony drives, though. More
information at http://makecd.core.de/.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
              NEW VERSIONS OF TEXTEDITOR.MCC AND BETTERSTRING.MCC
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Allan Odgaard (Duff@DIKU.DK) has released new versions of two of his classes.
Two new tags have been added to TextEditor.mcc and there is one new tag for
BetterString.mcc plus some other changes. Both classes can both be found at his
homepage: http://www.diku.dk/students/duff/

And here are direct links to the archives:

   - http://www.p2p-it.dk/duff/MCC_BetterString.LZX
   - http://www.p2p-it.dk/duff/MCC_TextEditor.LZX
