@node not00 "EDITORIAL : I AM, I SAID"
    ___________                                               ______________
---| EDITORIAL |---------------------------------------------| I AM, I SAID |---
    ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯                                               ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Hello and welcome to the 23rd issue of AmiChannel News.

"Have you ever heard of the last product from Amiga Inc.? Mmmm, the socks or the
cake. The new brand multimillion dollar SDK. And the Amiga developer comunity is
starring... as the dissapointed people who bought it."

Well, apart from this bad joke, the SDK is out and the first impressions are
more negative than positive. I am afraid that we have been deceived by someone.
Why? Probably you have heard of the several demostrations Amiga did in Amiga
shows like Amiga 2k in San Louis or in the World of Alternatives in Neuss
(Germany). Bill showed there some GRAPHICS demos of the new AMIE. The key here
is GRAPHICS.

Well, I have spoken with a friend of mine who has just bought it and hes very
dissapointed as the SDK does not include any MULTIMEDIA capability (d'oh) and
the only way to kill a process is... to kill Elate. Not nice, for sure.

The first problem is more a question of development. But, we thought that
everyting was progressing fast enough so the user version of AMIE would be ready
for Christmas. I am afraid that this would not be possible.

The second problem is more a question related of Virtual Processor design. It
comes from cellular phones and the killing of processes do not make sense in
these devices. But this feature is essential in a desktop environment.

Conclusions? Amiga Inc. have a long distance to walk and the future is not so
bright as we thought.

Before I forgot, if you can read french take a look at the Obligment magazine.
The last issue is now available at
http://www.netlinker.com/amigapower/indexAP.html. It's worth the reading, mate.

That's everything I wanted to say. Remember to visit the SAUG website, which is
located in:

	http://www.saug.org/

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

	noticias@saug.org

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
Angel Alvarez Díaz - noticias@saug.org
Editor of the e-magazine AmiChannel News
Responsible of the News Departament of S.A.U.G and Mundo Amiga
Member of C.U.A.E Nº 293 - FOREIGN DIRECTOR
